---
import CalculatorPage from '../../components/CalculatorPage.astro';
import NoiseDoseCalculator from '../../components/NoiseDoseCalculator.astro';
import { socialImages } from '../../data/social';
---

<CalculatorPage
  title="NIOSH noise dose calculator | dBcheck"
  description="Combine multiple sound-level and duration periods into one estimated daily occupational noise dose using the NIOSH 85 dBA, 8 hour and 3 dB model."
  kicker="Noise Dose Calculator"
  heading="One day can contain many exposures."
  intro="Combine several approximately constant sound levels and durations into one estimated NIOSH daily occupational reference dose."
  socialImage={socialImages.exposure}
>
  <NoiseDoseCalculator />

  <Fragment slot="references">
    <section>
      <span class="kicker">How it works</span>
      <h2>Each period uses part of the dose</h2>
      <p>The calculator finds the NIOSH reference duration for each level, divides the entered duration by that reference and adds the percentages. <a href="/articles/what-is-noise-dose/">Read what noise dose means</a>.</p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <span class="kicker">Named framework</span>
      <h2>NIOSH occupational model</h2>
      <p>The model uses 85 dBA for 8 hours and halves the reference duration for each 3 dB increase. See the <a href="https://www.cdc.gov/niosh/noise/about/noise.html">NIOSH guidance</a>.</p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <span class="kicker">Important limits</span>
      <h2>An estimate, not personal advice</h2>
      <p>Changing levels, impulse noise and uncertain phone readings need more context. The percentage is not a medical result or an individual safety guarantee.</p>
    </section>
  </Fragment>
</CalculatorPage>
